# Backend Deployment 

## Requirements

 Java Development Kit install.
 Maven installed.

## Step 1: Install Java

1. To confirm whether Java is already installed on your system, execute the following command in your terminal or command prompt:

   ```bash
   java -version
   ```

## Step 2: Install Maven

Installing maven in ubuntu:

```shell
apt install maven -y
```

## To confirm whether Maven is already installed on your system, execute the following command in your terminal or command prompt:

```bash
mvn -version
```

## Create backend/Dockerfile:

FROM maven:3.8.3-openjdk-17
COPY . /opt/
WORKDIR /opt
COPY application.properties src/main/resources/application.properties
RUN mvn clean package
WORKDIR /opt/target
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["java","-jar","student-registration-backend-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar"]

## Step 3: Build backend image

docker build -t backend-app.


## 4 : Step 4: Run backend container
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 backend-app

